Global Intumescent Coating for Steel Market Insights
Intumescent Coating for Steel Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 10.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Intumescent Coating for Steel Market Overview
The global market for intumescent coating for steel was valued at approximately USD 3.2 billion in 2024 and is expected to expand at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 5.6% during the forecast period from 2024 to 2032. The increasing demand for fire protection in industrial and commercial construction, along with growing regulations around fire safety, is driving the growth of the market. These coatings are widely used in infrastructure projects to enhance the safety and durability of steel structures exposed to high temperatures. The market is also witnessing a rise in government investments in fire safety technologies, which is expected to further stimulate the demand for intumescent coatings. As industries become more focused on sustainable and safe construction, the market will continue to experience substantial growth.

